raylib
------------------------------------------
raylib is highly inspired by Borland BGI graphics lib and by XNA framework and
it's specially well suited for prototyping, tooling, graphical applications,
embedded systems and education.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.0.7-1
  libraylib-devel-2.5.0-1bl1
  libraylib2-2.5.0-1bl1
  libX11-devel-1.6.5-1
  libX11_6-1.6.5-1
  pkg-config-1.6.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.13.1-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-7.4.0-1
  gcc-objc-7.4.0-1
  ninja-1.9.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/raysan5/raylib

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/raysan5/raylib/archive/2.5.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack raylib-2.5.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./raylib-2.5.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/raylib-2.5.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/raylib-2.5.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libraylib2-2.5.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libraylib-devel-2.5.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(raylib)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/raylib.README
  /usr/share/doc/raylib/BINDINGS.md
  /usr/share/doc/raylib/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md
  /usr/share/doc/raylib/CONTRIBUTING.md
  /usr/share/doc/raylib/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/raylib/HISTORY.md
  /usr/share/doc/raylib/LICENSE.md
  /usr/share/doc/raylib/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/raylib/ROADMAP.md

(libraylib2)
  /usr/bin/cygraylib-2.dll

(libraylib-devel)
  /usr/include/raylib.h
  /usr/lib/cmake/raylib/raylib-config-version.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/raylib/raylib-config.cmake
  /usr/lib/libraylib.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/raylib.pc

